236
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:17,239
At first look, you'd
think this is

237
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:20,639
the worst place on Earth...
A ravaged, toxic,

238
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:23,933
godforsaken hill
threatened from above,

239
00:11:23,975 --> 00:11:26,102
riddled with darkness below.

240
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:28,729
But you'd be wrong.

241
00:11:28,771 --> 00:11:32,733
Butte, Montana... it is,
in fact, heartbreakingly,

242
00:11:32,775 --> 00:11:34,528
poignantly beautiful.

243
00:11:34,569 --> 00:11:38,302
The gallus frames seem
eyesores for only a second

244
00:11:38,303 --> 00:11:41,180
before it becomes clear
why they are points

245
00:11:41,181 --> 00:11:44,266
of fierce pride for locals,
for whom they signify

246
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:45,913
and commemorate everything.

247
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,957
For Montanans, many
people consider it

248
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:49,459
sort of a black eye.

249
00:11:49,501 --> 00:11:53,129
I happen to think it's sort
of the essence of Montana.

250
00:11:53,171 --> 00:11:54,922
Aaron Parrett was born in Butte.

251
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,591
He's a professor of literature

252
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:59,553
